name: Block Island Rock Journal #1001
description:
Original design and photograph by Karl Heine of DesignerJournals™. This eco-friendly journal features a rich image of Block Island rocks. Perfect for recording notes or making sketches at PUSH Block Island Design Camp!

Size: 8.5" 5.5" (Landscape)
Cover: 110 dtc Mohawk® |  Matte laminated with removable label
Interior sheets: 75 pages — smooth surface Mohawk® Options text weight acid-free paper, 100% PCW. Bleed-proof even when writing or drawing with a Sharpie® permanent marker. Wire coil binding: 90% recycled steel.
Back: 24pt Wetsuit recycled rubberized stock

name: Block Island blank note cards
description:
An eclectic collection of Block Island — nature. From rocks close up to pristine beach settings from hidden coves around the island. Shot by Karl Heine over many year's of exploration, this series is on going.

Box set of 10 images with envelopes.
